<DocsPageTitle Path="Migration">
    Blazorise 2.0 Migration CLI
</DocsPageTitle>

<DocsPageLead>
    Blazorise.Migrator is a command-line tool that inspects your solution or project and guides you through moving to Blazorise 2.0.
</DocsPageLead>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    Start with <Code>analyze</Code> to understand what will change. When you are comfortable with the report, use <Code>migrate</Code> to apply the updates.
</DocsPageParagraph>

<DocsPageSubtitle>
    Install
</DocsPageSubtitle>

<DocsPageSection>
    <DocsPageSectionHeader>
        Install the global tool from NuGet.
    </DocsPageSectionHeader>
    <DocsPageSectionSource Code="MigrationInstallExample" />
</DocsPageSection>

<DocsPageSection>
    <DocsPageSectionHeader Title="Minimal smoke test">
        Confirm the tool is available on your path.
    </DocsPageSectionHeader>
    <DocsPageSectionSource Code="MigrationSmokeTestExample" />
</DocsPageSection>

<DocsPageSubtitle>
    Recommended workflow
</DocsPageSubtitle>

<DocsPageSection>
    <DocsPageSectionHeader>
        Follow this sequence for a safe, reviewable migration.
    </DocsPageSectionHeader>
    <DocsPageSectionContent>
        <OrderedList>
            <OrderedListItem>Analyze the solution or project to see what will change.</OrderedListItem>
            <OrderedListItem>Use <Code>--json</Code> if you want to keep a report for review.</OrderedListItem>
            <OrderedListItem>Run <Code>migrate</Code> with <Code>--dry-run</Code> to preview file edits.</OrderedListItem>
            <OrderedListItem>Run <Code>migrate</Code> again with <Code>--backup</Code> to apply changes and keep <Code>.bak</Code> files.</OrderedListItem>
        </OrderedList>
    </DocsPageSectionContent>
    <DocsPageSectionSource Code="MigrationExamplesExample" />
</DocsPageSection>

<DocsPageSection>
    <DocsPageSectionHeader Title="Analyze">
        Analyze a solution or project for Blazorise 2.0 migration. This command always runs in dry-run mode.
    </DocsPageSectionHeader>
    <DocsPageSectionContent>
        <Paragraph>
            When <Code>--path</Code> is omitted, the current directory is used. You can pass a folder, <Code>.sln</Code>, <Code>.slnx</Code>, or <Code>.csproj</Code>.
        </Paragraph>
    </DocsPageSectionContent>
    <DocsPageSectionSource Code="MigrationAnalyzeCommandExample" />
</DocsPageSection>

<DocsPageSubtitle>
    Migrate
</DocsPageSubtitle>

<DocsPageSection>
    <DocsPageSectionHeader Title="Apply changes">
        Apply Blazorise 2.0 migration changes to projects that reference Blazorise packages.
    </DocsPageSectionHeader>
    <DocsPageSectionContent>
        <Paragraph>
            When <Code>--path</Code> is omitted, the current directory is used. Use <Code>--dry-run</Code> to preview changes and <Code>--backup</Code> to keep <Code>.bak</Code> files.
        </Paragraph>
    </DocsPageSectionContent>
    <DocsPageSectionSource Code="MigrationMigrateCommandExample" />
</DocsPageSection>

<DocsPageSubtitle>
    Options
</DocsPageSubtitle>

<DocsAttributes Title="Analyze options" Ordered="false">
    <DocsAttributesItem Name="--path &lt;path&gt;" Type="string" Default="current directory">
        <Paragraph>
            Accepts a folder, <Code>.sln</Code>, <Code>.slnx</Code>, or <Code>.csproj</Code>.
        </Paragraph>
    </DocsAttributesItem>
    <DocsAttributesItem Name="--json &lt;file&gt;" Type="string" Default="none">
        <Paragraph>
            Write the analysis report to the specified file path.
        </Paragraph>
    </DocsAttributesItem>
    <DocsAttributesItem Name="--all-projects" Type="bool" Default="false">
        <Paragraph>
            Ignore solution files and scan all projects under the path, even if they do not reference Blazorise packages.
        </Paragraph>
    </DocsAttributesItem>
    <DocsAttributesItem Name="--verbose" Type="bool" Default="false">
        <Paragraph>
            Emit detailed diagnostics while scanning.
        </Paragraph>
    </DocsAttributesItem>
</DocsAttributes>

